---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="About KikuAI Lab and our philosophy">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="mb-10">About</h1>
      
      <div class="space-y-10">
        <section class="space-y-6 text-content">
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
            KikuAI Lab is a laboratory for building autonomous AI micro-products. We believe in the power of focused, single-purpose tools that solve real problems. Our philosophy is simple: <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">one function, one product</strong>. Each service we build does one thing exceptionally well, without the bloat of trying to be everything to everyone. This approach allows us to iterate quickly, maintain high quality, and deliver value faster.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Autonomy</strong> is at the core of everything we build. Our products are self-contained services that run independently, with minimal dependencies and clear interfaces. This makes them reliable, scalable, and easy to integrate into existing workflows. We don't build monolithic platforms—we build focused tools that work together when needed, but stand alone when they don't.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
            We're <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">market-first, not tech-first</strong>. Every product starts with a real problem that needs solving, not a cool technology looking for a use case. We focus on the Western market, where users value simplicity, reliability, and clear value propositions. Our distribution strategy relies on passive channels—SEO, word-of-mouth, and organic discovery—rather than aggressive marketing. This ensures our work has immediate value and clear purpose.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Minimalism and accessibility</strong> guide our design decisions. We build products that are easy to understand, easy to use, and accessible to everyone. No unnecessary complexity, no hidden features, no learning curve. If a feature doesn't directly solve the problem, it doesn't belong. This commitment to simplicity makes our products more reliable, more maintainable, and more valuable to users.
          </p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="mt-12">
          <h2 class="mb-8">Principles</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-5 list-none">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">One function, one product</strong> — Each service solves exactly one problem, exceptionally well
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Autonomous by design</strong> — Self-contained services with minimal dependencies and clear interfaces
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Market-first approach</strong> — Start with real problems, not cool technologies
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Passive distribution</strong> — Rely on SEO, word-of-mouth, and organic discovery
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Western market focus</strong> — Build for users who value simplicity and reliability
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Minimalism</strong> — No unnecessary complexity, no hidden features, no learning curve
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Accessibility</strong> — Products that are easy to understand, use, and accessible to everyone
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="text-lg text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Open source</strong> — Transparent, auditable, and community-driven development
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
